EqlMemberSEDShareType.name: EqlMemberSEDShareType
EqlMemberSEDShareType.description: A share of an SED encryption key.

eqlMemberIndex.name: eqlMemberIndex
eqlMemberIndex.description: This field unique identifies an array within a group.

eqlMemberDateAndTime.name: eqlMemberDateAndTime
eqlMemberDateAndTime.description: This field is dynamic, it contains the date and time for the array. There is no default value.

eqlMemberTimeZone.name: eqlMemberTimeZone
eqlMemberTimeZone.description: The field specifies the default timezone for the group. This can be overwritten on a per Array basis. The default is EST. We need to file in all the supported TZ. For now we punt and do GMT as the catch all.

eqlMemberAdjustDaylightSavTime.name: eqlMemberAdjustDaylightSavTime
eqlMemberAdjustDaylightSavTime.description: This field specifies whether or not dayLight savings time should be applied to the time. The default value is enabled.

eqlMemberDefaultRoute.name: eqlMemberDefaultRoute
eqlMemberDefaultRoute.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlMemberSite.name: eqlMemberSite
eqlMemberSite.description: This field specifies the site where the volume res ides. Sites are defined on a per array basis. Sites are used to define where primary and secondary copies of volume mirror reside. The default is the default site.

eqlMemberDescription.name: eqlMemberDescription
eqlMemberDescription.description: This field contains a description of the array. For example the location of the array. There is no default.

eqlMemberUUID.name: eqlMemberUUID
eqlMemberUUID.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field is for internal use only.

eqlMemberName.name: eqlMemberName
eqlMemberName.description: This field specifies the name of the array. This name must be unique within the group. It can be a DNS name, though it is not required to be one. There is no default.

eqlMemberRowStatus.name: eqlMemberRowStatus
eqlMemberRowStatus.description: This RowStatus is used only to delete a member. The row in this table could be created only by the subsystem.

eqlMemberState.name: eqlMemberState
eqlMemberState.description: The field specifies the desired state of the array. Currently setting this value to vacate is the only operation that is supported.

eqlMemberPolicySingleControllerSafe.name: eqlMemberPolicySingleControllerSafe
eqlMemberPolicySingleControllerSafe.description: This field specifies the cache policy if we boot with only one CM.

eqlMemberPolicyLowBatterySafe.name: eqlMemberPolicyLowBatterySafe
eqlMemberPolicyLowBatterySafe.description: This field specifies the cache policy if the battery charge is below tolerance.

eqlMemberVersion.name: eqlMemberVersion
eqlMemberVersion.description: This field specifies the compatibility level of a member.

eqlMemberDelayDataMove.name: eqlMemberDelayDataMove
eqlMemberDelayDataMove.description: When a new member is added to the group the value of this column will be zero(unconfigured). Before configuring raid-policy , this value must be set to wait(1) or use-member-space(2). The value can be changed from wait(1) to use-member-space(2) But once set to use-member-space, it cannot be changed back.

eqlMemberDefaultInetRouteType.name: eqlMemberDefaultInetRouteType
eqlMemberDefaultInetRouteType.description: This field is used to indicate the default gateway for the group. This value can be overriden on a per array basis. This field contains the address of the local router used to forward network traffic beyond the local subnet. Gateways are used to connect multiple subnets. There is no default value for this entry.

eqlMemberDefaultInetRoute.name: eqlMemberDefaultInetRoute
eqlMemberDefaultInetRoute.description: This field is used to indicate the default gateway for the group. This value can be overriden on a per array basis. This field contains the address of the local router used to forward network traffic beyond the local subnet. Gateways are used to connect multiple subnets. There is no default value for this entry.

eqlMemberDriveMirroring.name: eqlMemberDriveMirroring
eqlMemberDriveMirroring.description: On disk drive failures, this value is checked for mirroring the data onto the spare drive. The value can be changed from enabled(0) to disabled(1) and vice-versa

eqlMemberProfileIndex.name: eqlMemberProfileIndex
eqlMemberProfileIndex.description: This field represents the profile identifier supported by this member.

eqlMemberControllerType.name: eqlMemberControllerType
eqlMemberControllerType.description: This variable specifies the type of the active controller module on this member. Ex: Type II

eqlMemberControllerMajorVersion.name: eqlMemberControllerMajorVersion
eqlMemberControllerMajorVersion.description: This variable specifies the major version number of the software present on the active controller module.

eqlMemberControllerMinorVersion.name: eqlMemberControllerMinorVersion
eqlMemberControllerMinorVersion.description: This variable specifies the minor version number of the software present on the active controller module.

eqlMemberControllerMaintenanceVersion.name: eqlMemberControllerMaintenanceVersion
eqlMemberControllerMaintenanceVersion.description: This variable specifies the maintenance version number of the software present on the active controller module.

eqlMemberCompressionCapable.name: eqlMemberCompressionCapable
eqlMemberCompressionCapable.description: This variable specifies if the member is capable of supporting compression.

eqlMemberStatusEntry.name: eqlMemberStatusEntry
eqlMemberStatusEntry.description: An entry (row) containing member status info

eqlMemberStatusTotalSpace.name: eqlMemberStatusTotalSpace
eqlMemberStatusTotalSpace.description: This field specifies the total disk space in MBs on the this array.

eqlMemberStatusTotalSpaceUsed.name: eqlMemberStatusTotalSpaceUsed
eqlMemberStatusTotalSpaceUsed.description: This field specifies the total disk space in MBs allocated to volume data for this array.

eqlMemberStatusModel.name: eqlMemberStatusModel
eqlMemberStatusModel.description: This field specifies the model number for the array.

eqlMemberStatusSerialNumber.name: eqlMemberStatusSerialNumber
eqlMemberStatusSerialNumber.description: This field specifies the serial number for the array.

eqlMemberStatusNumberOfControllers.name: eqlMemberStatusNumberOfControllers
eqlMemberStatusNumberOfControllers.description: This field specifies the number of Controller modules in the array.

eqlMemberStatusNumberOfDisks.name: eqlMemberStatusNumberOfDisks
eqlMemberStatusNumberOfDisks.description: This field specifies the number of disks installed in the array.

eqlMemberStatusNumberOfSpares.name: eqlMemberStatusNumberOfSpares
eqlMemberStatusNumberOfSpares.description: This field specifies the number disks allocated as spares in an array.

eqlMemberStatusCacheSize.name: eqlMemberStatusCacheSize
eqlMemberStatusCacheSize.description: The field specifies the size in MB of the read/write cache within the array.

eqlMemberStatusCacheMode.name: eqlMemberStatusCacheMode
eqlMemberStatusCacheMode.description: This field specifies the mode the cache is in within the array. The default is write-back. The array will be set to write-thru on battery failure.

eqlMemberStatusNumberOfConnections.name: eqlMemberStatusNumberOfConnections
eqlMemberStatusNumberOfConnections.description: This field specifies the number of iSCSI initiators which are connected to this array.

eqlMemberStatusAverageTemp.name: eqlMemberStatusAverageTemp
eqlMemberStatusAverageTemp.description: This field specifies the average tempature of the array in degrees C.

eqlMemberStatusTempStatus.name: eqlMemberStatusTempStatus
eqlMemberStatusTempStatus.description: This field specifies whether the tempatures for the array are within acceptable tolerances. ** What are acceptable tolerances?

eqlMemberStatusBackplaneTempSensor1.name: eqlMemberStatusBackplaneTempSensor1
eqlMemberStatusBackplaneTempSensor1.description: This field specifies the tempature of backplane sensor 1 in degrees C.

eqlMemberStatusBackplaneTempSensor2.name: eqlMemberStatusBackplaneTempSensor2
eqlMemberStatusBackplaneTempSensor2.description: This field specifies the tempature of backplane sensor 2 in degrees C.

eqlMemberStatusPowerSupply1Status.name: eqlMemberStatusPowerSupply1Status
eqlMemberStatusPowerSupply1Status.description: This field specifies the state of the first power supply.

eqlMemberStatusPowerSupply2Status.name: eqlMemberStatusPowerSupply2Status
eqlMemberStatusPowerSupply2Status.description: This field specifies the state of the second power supply.

eqlMemberStatusTrayOneFanOneSpeed.name: eqlMemberStatusTrayOneFanOneSpeed
eqlMemberStatusTrayOneFanOneSpeed.description: The field specifies the rpm fan speed for fan tray 1, fan 1.

eqlMemberStatusTrayOneFanTwoSpeed.name: eqlMemberStatusTrayOneFanTwoSpeed
eqlMemberStatusTrayOneFanTwoSpeed.description: The field specifies the rpm fan speed for fan tray 1, fan 2.

eqlMemberStatusTrayTwoFanOneSpeed.name: eqlMemberStatusTrayTwoFanOneSpeed
eqlMemberStatusTrayTwoFanOneSpeed.description: The field specifies the rpm fan speed for fan tray 2, fan 1.

eqlMemberStatusTrayTwoFanTwoSpeed.name: eqlMemberStatusTrayTwoFanTwoSpeed
eqlMemberStatusTrayTwoFanTwoSpeed.description: The field specifies the rpm fan speed for fan tray 2, fan 2.

eqlMemberStatusPowerSupplyOneFanStatus.name: eqlMemberStatusPowerSupplyOneFanStatus
eqlMemberStatusPowerSupplyOneFanStatus.description: This field specifies whether the fan in power supply one is on-line or not.

eqlMemberStatusPowerSupplyTwoFanStatus.name: eqlMemberStatusPowerSupplyTwoFanStatus
eqlMemberStatusPowerSupplyTwoFanStatus.description: This field specifies whether the fan in power supply two is on-line or not.

eqlMemberStatusRaidStatus.name: eqlMemberStatusRaidStatus
eqlMemberStatusRaidStatus.description: This field specifies the status of the raid subsystem. This is a composite of the view of the underlying subsystems. Status ok means things are ok. Status degraded means we are in a degraded state, possible because no spare is available. Status verifying means a verify pass is run, and a percent complete is available. Status reconstructing means we are reconstructing a drive and a percent complete is available. Status failed means we had a failure while we were up, possibly a drive failed and we have no spare. Status catastrophicLoss may not be visible to the user since the member may not be able to bootup. It means we need administrator intervention to correct the problem.

eqlMemberStatusRaidPercentage.name: eqlMemberStatusRaidPercentage
eqlMemberStatusRaidPercentage.description: This field specifies the percentage complete when the eqlMemberStatusRaidStatus is verifying or reconstructing.

eqlMemberStatusLostRaidBlocks.name: eqlMemberStatusLostRaidBlocks
eqlMemberStatusLostRaidBlocks.description: This field specifies whether we have lost blocks in the raid array which the user may want to clear.

eqlMemberStatusHealth.name: eqlMemberStatusHealth
eqlMemberStatusHealth.description: This field specifies what the overall health of the member is on a scale of 0(dead) to 100(healthy) -- deprecated by new health tables in v1.1

eqlMemberStatusShortId.name: eqlMemberStatusShortId
eqlMemberStatusShortId.description: This field specifies short member address

eqlTargetMemberIndex.name: eqlTargetMemberIndex
eqlTargetMemberIndex.description: This is a duplication of eqlMemberIndex just to make our code generation happy.

eqlMemberInfoStatus.name: eqlMemberInfoStatus
eqlMemberInfoStatus.description: The current state of the member.

eqlMemberHealthEntry.name: eqlMemberHealthEntry
eqlMemberHealthEntry.description: An entry (row) containing overall member health info

eqlMemberHealthStatus.name: eqlMemberHealthStatus
eqlMemberHealthStatus.description: The value of this object is determinted by the severity of the health condition state variables. The most severe state will be reflected.

eqlMemberHealthWarningConditions.name: eqlMemberHealthWarningConditions
eqlMemberHealthWarningConditions.description: This field defines possible warning health conditions and which ones are present.

eqlMemberHealthCriticalConditions.name: eqlMemberHealthCriticalConditions
eqlMemberHealthCriticalConditions.description: This field defines possible critical health conditions and which ones are present.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureTable.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureTable
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Member Health Details Temperature Table.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureEntry.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureEntry
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureEntry.description: An entry (row) containing member health detailed temperature info

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTempSensorIndex.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTempSensorIndex
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTempSensorIndex.description: A unique integer that denotes which temperature sensor this entry refers to

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureName.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureName
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureName.description: This field specifies the name of the sensor that we display to the user.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureValue.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureValue
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureValue.description: The value of this object is temperature in degrees C

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureCurrent.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureCurrentState
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureCurrent.description: This field tells us the state of the temperature sensor. Either normal, warning or critical.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureHighCri.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureHighCriticalThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureHighCri.description: when the TemperatureValue is greater than or equal to this variable's value the current state is set to critical.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureHighWar.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureHighWarningThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureHighWar.description: when the TemperatureValue is greater than or equal to this variable's value and not greater than or equal to the HighCriticalThreshold, the current state is set to warning.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureLowCrit.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureLowCriticalThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureLowCrit.description: when the TemperatureValue is less than or equal to this variable's value the current state is set to critical.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureLowWarn.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureLowWarningThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureLowWarn.description: when the TemperatureValue is less than or equal to this variable's value and not less than or equal to the LowCriticalThreshold, the current state is set to warning.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureNameID.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureNameID
eqlMemberHealthDetailsTemperatureNameID.description: This field specifies the XML based name ID of the sensor that we display to the user.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanTable.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanTable
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Member Health Details Fan Table.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanEntry.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanEntry
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanEntry.description: An entry (row) containing member health detailed fan info

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanIndex.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanIndex
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanIndex.description: A unique integer that identifies the fan that the corresponding entry refers to

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanName.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanName
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanName.description: This field specifies the name of the fan that we display to the user.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanValue.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanValue
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanValue.description: The value of this object is fan speed in rpm.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanCurrentState.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanCurrentState
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanCurrentState.description: This field tells us the state of the fan. Either normal, warning or critical.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanHighCriticalThr.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanHighCriticalThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanHighCriticalThr.description: when the FanValue is greater than or equal to this variable's value the current state is set to critical.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanHighWarningThre.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanHighWarningThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanHighWarningThre.description: when the FanValue is greater than or equal to this variable's value and not greater than or equal to the HighCriticalThreshold, the current state is set to warning.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanLowCriticalThre.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanLowCriticalThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanLowCriticalThre.description: when the FanValue is less than or equal to this variable's value the current state is set to critical.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanLowWarningThres.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanLowWarningThreshold
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanLowWarningThres.description: when the FanValue is less than or equal to this variable's value and not less than or equal to the LowCriticalThreshold, the current state is set to warning.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanNameID.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanNameID
eqlMemberHealthDetailsFanNameID.description: This field specifies the XML based name ID of the fan that we display to the user.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyTable.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyTable
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Member Health Details Power Supply Table. The mappng of index to power supply: .1 = power supply 0 .2 = power supply 1 .3 = power supply 2

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyEntry.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyEntry
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyEntry.description: An entry (row) containing power supply status information.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyIndex.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyIndex
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyIndex.description: Iff the power supply current state is on-and-operating, then this field tells if the fan is operational.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyName.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyName
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyName.description: This field specifies the name of the power supply that we display to the user.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyCurrent.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyCurrentState
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyCurrent.description: This field tells us the state of the power supply.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyFanStat.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyFanStatus
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyFanStat.description: Iff the power supply current state is on-and-operating, then this field tells if the fan is operational.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyFirmwar.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyFirmwareVersion
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyFirmwar.description: This field specifies power supply firmware version. Only available starting from Porfidio Platforms.

eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyNameID.name: eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyNameID
eqlMemberHealthDetailsPowerSupplyNameID.description: This field specifies the XML based nameID of the power supply that we display to the user.

eqlMemberIdentificationEntry.name: eqlMemberIdentificationEntry
eqlMemberIdentificationEntry.description: List of attributes of the array used to identity the location of that array.

eqlMemberIdentificationLEDsBlinking.name: eqlMemberIdentificationLEDsBlinking
eqlMemberIdentificationLEDsBlinking.description: Setting this variable to true enables blinking of the ALRM and WARN LEDs on the front panel and the ERR LED on the CM, as seen from the back. The blinking stops after 2 hours or when the variable is set to false.

eqlMemberStorageEntry.name: eqlMemberStorageEntry
eqlMemberStorageEntry.description: List of attributes used to convey the details of storage space utilization on the array.

eqlMemberTotalStorage.name: eqlMemberTotalStorage
eqlMemberTotalStorage.description: This field specifies the total disk storage in MBs on the array.

eqlMemberUsedStorage.name: eqlMemberUsedStorage
eqlMemberUsedStorage.description: This field specifies sum of reserved delegated space, reserved volume space, used snapshot space, used replication space.

eqlMemberSnapStorage.name: eqlMemberSnapStorage
eqlMemberSnapStorage.description: This field specifies used snapshot space. Space on this array used by snapshots. Note that this value is not the same as space reserved for snapshots.

eqlMemberReplStorage.name: eqlMemberReplStorage
eqlMemberReplStorage.description: This field specifies used replication space. Space on this array used by in progress replicas or failback replicas. Note that this value is not the same as space reserved for replication.

eqlMemberVirtualStorage.name: eqlMemberVirtualStorage
eqlMemberVirtualStorage.description: This field specifies the amount of space (MB) used by compressed pages if all pages were not compressed on the member.

eqlMemberCompressionStackStorage.name: eqlMemberCompressionStackStorage
eqlMemberCompressionStackStorage.description: The amount of space (MB) used to store compressed data on this member.

eqlMemberChassisEntry.name: eqlMemberChassisEntry
eqlMemberChassisEntry.description: List of attributes used to convey the details and type of Chassis present on the array.

eqlMemberModel.name: eqlMemberModel
eqlMemberModel.description: This field specifies the model number for the array.

eqlMemberSerialNumber.name: eqlMemberSerialNumber
eqlMemberSerialNumber.description: This field specifies the serial number for the array.

eqlMemberNumberOfControllers.name: eqlMemberNumberOfControllers
eqlMemberNumberOfControllers.description: This field specifies the number of Controller modules in the array.

eqlMemberNumberOfDisks.name: eqlMemberNumberOfDisks
eqlMemberNumberOfDisks.description: This field specifies the number of disk installed in the array.

eqlMemberCacheSize.name: eqlMemberCacheSize
eqlMemberCacheSize.description: The field specifies the size in MB of the read/write cache within the array.

eqlMemberCacheMode.name: eqlMemberCacheMode
eqlMemberCacheMode.description: This field specifies the mode the cache is in within the array. The default is write-back. The array will be set to write-thru on battery failure.

eqlMemberChassisType.name: eqlMemberChassisType
eqlMemberChassisType.description: This field specifies the chassis type of the array. The default is unknown.

eqlMemberServiceTag.name: eqlMemberServiceTag
eqlMemberServiceTag.description: This field specifies the service tag number for the array.

eqlMemberProductFamily.name: eqlMemberProductFamily
eqlMemberProductFamily.description: This field specifies the product family of the peer storage array. Ex: PS5000 E Series.

eqlMemberChassisFlags.name: eqlMemberChassisFlags
eqlMemberChassisFlags.description: This field defines the common place holder for Chassis operational flags. The flags must be of type enable(1) or disable(0), and the default will always be disable(0).

eqlMemberChassisDiskSectorSize.name: eqlMemberChassisDiskSectorSize
eqlMemberChassisDiskSectorSize.description: This field specifies the disk sector size of disks in this array.

eqlMemberConnEntry.name: eqlMemberConnEntry
eqlMemberConnEntry.description: List of attributes used to convey the connections information on the array.

eqlMemberNumberOfConnections.name: eqlMemberNumberOfConnections
eqlMemberNumberOfConnections.description: This field specifies the number of iSCSI connections made from initiators to this array.

eqlMemberReadLatency.name: eqlMemberReadLatency
eqlMemberReadLatency.description: The accumulative latency in milli seconds for read operations on this member. The value will be zero until all members are atleast 3.0. The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberWriteLatency.name: eqlMemberWriteLatency
eqlMemberWriteLatency.description: The accumulative latency in milli seconds for write operations on this member. The value will be zero until all members are atleast 3.0. The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberReadAvgLatency.name: eqlMemberReadAvgLatency
eqlMemberReadAvgLatency.description: The average latency for read operations on this member in milli seconds. The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberWriteAvgLatency.name: eqlMemberWriteAvgLatency
eqlMemberWriteAvgLatency.description: The average latency for write operations on this member in milli seconds. The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberReadOpCount.name: eqlMemberReadOpCount
eqlMemberReadOpCount.description: The number of read operations on this member. The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberWriteOpCount.name: eqlMemberWriteOpCount
eqlMemberWriteOpCount.description: The number of write operations on this member. The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberTxData.name: eqlMemberTxData
eqlMemberTxData.description: The count of data octets trasmitted by this member.The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberRxData.name: eqlMemberRxData
eqlMemberRxData.description: The count of data octets received by this member.The value is reset to zero upon reboot.

eqlMemberNumberOfExtConnections.name: eqlMemberNumberOfExtConnections
eqlMemberNumberOfExtConnections.description: This field specifies the number of iSCSI connections made from external initiators to this array.

eqlMemberRAIDEntry.name: eqlMemberRAIDEntry
eqlMemberRAIDEntry.description: List of attributes used to convey the RAID status information on the array.

eqlMemberRaidStatus.name: eqlMemberRaidStatus
eqlMemberRaidStatus.description: This field specifies the status of the raid subsystem. This is a composite of the view of the underlying subsystems. Status ok means things are ok. Status degraded means we are in a degraded state, possible because no spare is available. Status verifying means a verify pass is run, and a percent complete is available. Status reconstructing means we are reconstructing a drive and a percent complete is available. Status failed means we had a failure while we were up, possibly a drive failed and we have no spare. Status catastrophicLoss may not be visible to the user since the member may not be able to bootup. It means we need administrator intervention to correct the problem. Status mirroring means we are mirroring a bad drive onto a spare drive.

eqlMemberRaidPercentage.name: eqlMemberRaidPercentage
eqlMemberRaidPercentage.description: This field specifies the percentage complete when the eqlMemberStatusRaidStatus is verifying or reconstructing.

eqlMemberLostRaidBlocks.name: eqlMemberLostRaidBlocks
eqlMemberLostRaidBlocks.description: This field specifies whether we have lost blocks in the raid array which the user may want to clear.

eqlMemberNumberOfSpares.name: eqlMemberNumberOfSpares
eqlMemberNumberOfSpares.description: This field specifies the number disks allocated as spares in an array.

eqlMemberRaidProgress.name: eqlMemberRaidProgress
eqlMemberRaidProgress.description: This field specifies 1000 times the percentage complete when the eqlMemberStatusRaidStatus is verifying or reconstructing.

eqlMemberPSGMapEntry.name: eqlMemberPSGMapEntry
eqlMemberPSGMapEntry.description: List of attributes used to convey the PSS ID information of this array in the group map.

eqlMemberShortId.name: eqlMemberShortId
eqlMemberShortId.description: This field specifies PSS ID of the member in the context of the leader of the PSG.

eqlMemberHealthTempSensorHighThreshold.name: eqlMemberHealthTempSensorHighThreshold
eqlMemberHealthTempSensorHighThreshold.description: Sent when a high threshold has been exceeded for any of the enclosure temp sensors. The implementation of this trap should not send more than one notification of this type for a sensor in any 10 minute time span

eqlMemberHealthTempSensorLowThreshold.name: eqlMemberHealthTempSensorLowThreshold
eqlMemberHealthTempSensorLowThreshold.description: Sent when a low threshold has been exceeded for any of the enclosure temp sensors. The implementation of this trap should not send more than one notification of this type for a sensor in any 10 minute time span

eqlMemberHealthFanSpeedHighThreshold.name: eqlMemberHealthFanSpeedHighThreshold
eqlMemberHealthFanSpeedHighThreshold.description: Sent when a high threshold has been exceeded for any of the enclosure fan speed sensors. The implementation of this trap should not send more than one notification of this type for a sensor in any 10 minute time span

eqlMemberHealthFanSpeedLowThreshold.name: eqlMemberHealthFanSpeedLowThreshold
eqlMemberHealthFanSpeedLowThreshold.description: Sent when a low threshold has been exceeded for any of the enclosure fan speed sensors. The implementation of this trap should not send more than one notification of this type for a sensor in any 10 minute time span

eqlMemberHealthPowerSupplyFanFailure.name: eqlMemberHealthPowerSupplyFanFailure
eqlMemberHealthPowerSupplyFanFailure.description: Sent when a failure has been detected on any of the power supply fan speed sensors. The implementation of this trap should not send more than one notification of this type for a sensor in any 10 minute time span

eqlMemberHealthPowerSupplyFailure.name: eqlMemberHealthPowerSupplyFailure
eqlMemberHealthPowerSupplyFailure.description: Sent when a failure has been detected on any of the power supplys in the PSA. The implementation of this trap should not send more than one notification of this type for a sensor in any 10 minute time span

eqlMemberHealthRAIDSetDoubleFaulted.name: eqlMemberHealthRAIDSetDoubleFaulted
eqlMemberHealthRAIDSetDoubleFaulted.description: Sent when the raid set has been detected to have double faulted. When this occurs, the array will not come up. User intervention is required to correct the issue

eqlMemberHealthBothFanTraysRemoved.name: eqlMemberHealthBothFanTraysRemoved
eqlMemberHealthBothFanTraysRemoved.description: Sent when both of the fan trays have been removed from the chassis. This results in overheating

eqlMemberHealthRAIDlostCache.name: eqlMemberHealthRAIDlostCache
eqlMemberHealthRAIDlostCache.description: Sent because the RAID driver is unable to recover the battery-backed cache. The disk array will not initialize without user intervention. See the Handling Lost Data section in the Group Administration manual for more information.

eqlMemberHealthFanTrayRemoved.name: eqlMemberHealthFanTrayRemoved
eqlMemberHealthFanTrayRemoved.description: Sent when one of the fan trays have been removed from the chassis. This results in overheating

eqlMemberHealthRAIDSetLostBlkTableFull.name: eqlMemberHealthRAIDSetLostBlkTableFull
eqlMemberHealthRAIDSetLostBlkTableFull.description: Sent when the RAID lost block table is full. This usually is an indication of lost data.

eqlMemberHealthBatteryLessThan72Hours.name: eqlMemberHealthBatteryLessThan72Hours
eqlMemberHealthBatteryLessThan72Hours.description: Sent when the battery has insufficient charge to survive a 72 hour power outage.

eqlMemberHealthRaidOrphanCache.name: eqlMemberHealthRaidOrphanCache
eqlMemberHealthRaidOrphanCache.description: Sent when the RAID driver finds data in the battery-backed cache with no matching disk array. Initialization will not proceed without user intervention. Call EqualLogic Support for assistance.

eqlMemberHealthRaidMultipleRaidSets.name: eqlMemberHealthRaidMultipleRaidSets
eqlMemberHealthRaidMultipleRaidSets.description: Sent when multiple valid RAIDsets were found. The array cannot choose which one to initialize. Remove all but one valid RAIDset and power-cycle the array.

eqlMemberHealthNVRAMBatteryFailed.name: eqlMemberHealthNVRAMBatteryFailed
eqlMemberHealthNVRAMBatteryFailed.description: Sent when the NVRAM battery fails . The NVRAM can no longer be used.

eqlMemberHealthhwComponentFailedCrit.name: eqlMemberHealthhwComponentFailedCrit
eqlMemberHealthhwComponentFailedCrit.description: Sent when a critical hardware component has failed.
